OL,3,CJeremy Kyle Show guest 'distraught'
OL,4,Cafter recording, landlady tells inquest
OL,6,FMrs Thaxter added: "He wasn't a happy
OL,7,Fman and he wasn't a well man, at times
OL,8,Fhe could hardly walk."
OL,10,FShe said that after the show
OL,11,Frecording, Mr Dymond, in a
OL,12,F"distraught" state, asked to stay
OL,13,Fagain at her home.
OL,15,F"He literally had nowhere else to go,
OL,16,Fhe said he had called his mum but she
OL,17,Fdidn't want to have anything to do
OL,18,Fwith him," she said.
OL,20,F"He was crying, I have never seen a
OL,21,Fman crying like that, he was so upset."
